a4b2f738-f0b0-400d-b685-987dfb90ba8c	61634547-13aa-47cd-94be-32191a6c8a44	en	<p>This panel groups related controls and information for the surrounding section. Hover any element to see its address; click the help hexagon to open this popover.</p>	library	64c8cf7d-1023-4d0d-bb53-b171bee89cc0	f	2026-05-04 03:13:34.596319+00	\N	2026-05-04 03:13:34.596319+00	\N	[]	[]
5f6cc07c-da96-4426-b0b4-a4ab53678884	63e87a99-5ce5-4511-babb-5f764461fcfe	en	<p>This is the live picture of your organisation. Each card is a part of the business — a division, an office, a team — and the lines show who reports to whom.</p><p><strong>What you can do here:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Click</strong> a card to select it. The right-hand panel opens so you can edit its name, colour and description.</li><li><strong>Double-click</strong> a card to centre it on screen.</li><li><strong>Right-click</strong> a card for a quick menu — add a child, edit, duplicate or delete.</li><li><strong>Drag</strong> a card onto another card to move it (and everything beneath it) to a new parent. You will be asked to confirm before anything changes.</li></ul><p>Use the toolbar at the top to flip the chart between top-down and left-to-right, switch between curved and right-angled connectors, fit everything on screen, or expand the chart to fill the whole window.</p>	manual	\N	f	2026-05-04 03:38:23.397467+00	\N	2026-05-04 03:20:54.517038+00	Organisation chart	[]	[]
2998d552-e440-4ffe-90ff-61761f68e2e1	2cf5952f-b839-4207-b61e-98bd100efcc8	en	<p>A scrollable list of every part of your organisation, shown as an indented hierarchy. Useful when the chart is large and you want to find or jump to a specific node without panning around.</p><p><strong>How to use it:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Click</strong> a row to highlight that node on the chart.</li><li><strong>Double-click</strong> a row to fly the chart to it, keeping your current zoom level.</li><li><strong>The chevron next to a row</strong> collapses or expands its children, so you can hide branches you do not need to see right now.</li><li><strong>The chevron at the very top</strong> expands or collapses every branch at once.</li></ul><p>Drag the right edge of the panel to make it wider or narrower. Click the chevron on its left edge to pin it open or let it tuck away.</p>	manual	\N	f	2026-05-04 03:38:23.418877+00	\N	2026-05-04 03:20:54.517038+00	Tree view	[]	[]
dc440e93-b4c2-417e-8af5-ecfbccf3e0b8	582b5c16-f468-486f-945b-c1166cb169d6	en	<p>Edit the details of the node you have selected on the chart. Changes save automatically when you click out of a field, so there is no separate save button.</p><p><strong>What each field is for:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Name</strong> — what the node is called. This is the label that shows on the card and in the tree.</li><li><strong>Label</strong> — an optional short word that describes the <em>kind</em> of node (for example <em>Department</em>, <em>Office</em>, <em>Team</em>). It appears as a small tag on the card so people can tell different types of nodes apart.</li><li><strong>Description</strong> — a longer note explaining what this node owns and who it serves. Visible to anyone with access to the chart.</li><li><strong>Colour</strong> — pick a swatch to give the node a distinctive accent colour, or click the strike-through circle to let the system choose one for you.</li></ul><p>Close the panel with the × in the top-right or by pressing <strong>Esc</strong>.</p>	manual	\N	f	2026-05-04 03:38:23.525175+00	\N	2026-05-04 03:20:54.517038+00	Edit a node	[]	[]
