839d25e4-9830-4cdc-ae80-5f6eba1f00af	7d13c74a-88ea-42dc-a009-5d2425d5d9e7	en	<p>Edit the details of the node you have selected on the chart. Changes save automatically when you click out of a field, so there is no separate save button.</p><p><strong>What each field is for:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Name</strong> — what the node is called. This is the label that shows on the card and in the tree.</li><li><strong>Label</strong> — an optional short word that describes the <em>kind</em> of node (for example <em>Department</em>, <em>Office</em>, <em>Team</em>). It appears as a small tag on the card so people can tell different types of nodes apart.</li><li><strong>Description</strong> — a longer note explaining what this node owns and who it serves. Visible to anyone with access to the chart.</li><li><strong>Colour</strong> — pick a swatch to give the node a distinctive accent colour, or click the strike-through circle to let the system choose one for you.</li></ul><p>Close the panel with the × in the top-right or by pressing <strong>Esc</strong>.</p>	manual	\N	f	2026-05-04 03:43:49.897608+00	\N	2026-05-04 03:43:32.523862+00	Edit a node	[]	[]
d9ac12bd-6cda-439c-96f3-571b48facfa9	32f50fa6-3c93-4121-bee8-1d62715f52a7	en	<p>A scrollable list of every part of your organisation, shown as an indented hierarchy. Useful when the chart is large and you want to find or jump to a specific node without panning around.</p><p><strong>How to use it:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Click</strong> a row to highlight that node on the chart.</li><li><strong>Double-click</strong> a row to fly the chart to it, keeping your current zoom level.</li><li><strong>The chevron next to a row</strong> collapses or expands its children, so you can hide branches you do not need to see right now.</li><li><strong>The chevron at the very top</strong> expands or collapses every branch at once.</li></ul><p>Drag the right edge of the panel to make it wider or narrower. Click the chevron on its left edge to pin it open or let it tuck away.</p>	manual	\N	f	2026-05-04 03:43:49.897608+00	\N	2026-05-04 03:43:32.523862+00	Tree view	[]	[]
